  - random matrix theory
  - spectral overlap
  - time-free dynamics
abstract: >
  reach is a Python package for analyzing quantum state reachability
  using time-free spectral overlap criteria. Instead of asking whether
  one can reach a target state at a specific time, the analysis determines
  whether a target state lies within the reachable subspace spanned by a
  parameterized Hamiltonian family. The package provides Monte Carlo
  analysis over random matrix ensembles (GOE/GUE) with full reproducibility
  and publication-quality visualization tools.
